Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: IN CONFORMITY WITH THE PRACTICE FOLLOWED BY MOST AQUARIUMS, THE COLLECTION IS NOT PRESENTED IN THE ACCOMPANYING STATEMENTS OF FINANCIAL POSITION. CONTRIBUTED COLLECTION ITEMS ARE NOT REFLECTED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FOUNDATION IS COMMITTED TO APPLYING THE HIGHEST PROFESSIONAL STANDARDS TO THE CARE AND PRESERVATION OF ITS UNIQUE COLLECTION. EACH OF THE ITEMS IS CATALOGUED, PRESERVED AND CARED FOR, AND ACTIVITIES VERIFYING THEIR EXISTENCE AND ASSESSING THEIR CONDITION ARE PERFORMED CONTINUOUSLY. ACCESSIONS AND DEACCESSIONS ARE APPROVED BY THE FOUNDATION'S BOARD OF TRUSTEES AND THE PROCEEDS FROM DEACCESSIONS ARE USED SOLELY FOR THE ACQUISITION OF COLLECTION ITEMS.
THE COLLECTION OF ANIMALS ENABLES THE FOUNDATION TO ATTRACT THE PUBLIC TO BUY TICKETS IN ORDER TO INSPIRE CONSERVATION OF THE MARINE ENVIRONMENT THROUGH EDUCATION, RESEARCH AND SUSTAINABLE PRACTICES.
Management continually evaluates tax positions reflected in the Foundation's tax filings and does not believe that any material uncertain tax positions exist.
